113
00:07:17,470 --> 00:07:19,000
So they...

114
00:07:19,290 --> 00:07:19,730
Mom.

115
00:07:19,750 --> 00:07:20,270
Left.

116
00:07:21,390 --> 00:07:24,590
When we got married,

117
00:07:24,610 --> 00:07:26,060
he was the one who brought it up.

118
00:07:26,060 --> 00:07:28,190
He said, "How about we don't have kids?"

119
00:07:28,190 --> 00:07:29,390
I said, "Okay."

120
00:07:36,560 --> 00:07:37,130
I...

121
00:07:38,990 --> 00:07:39,610
So...

122
00:07:44,150 --> 00:07:46,270
So, you all knew that he would leave.

123
00:07:46,370 --> 00:07:46,970
Yes.

124
00:07:59,220 --> 00:08:00,540
♫I♫

125
00:08:02,380 --> 00:08:04,390
♫Like a migratory bird♫

126
00:08:06,640 --> 00:08:09,060
♫Flying around the world♫

127
00:08:09,700 --> 00:08:12,980
♫But having nowhere to stay♫

128
00:08:16,350 --> 00:08:17,530
♫Dream♫

129
00:08:19,580 --> 00:08:21,990
♫It's getting out of reach♫

