138
00:08:36,470 --> 00:08:39,860
♫Flicker with light♫

139
00:08:38,950 --> 00:08:40,640
I have high hopes for life.

140
00:08:41,000 --> 00:08:49,400
♫The night is deep, and the stars are dim♫

141
00:08:41,480 --> 00:08:44,210
On my husband Liu Ming's 30th birthday,

142
00:08:44,610 --> 00:08:45,390
when I was at home

143
00:08:45,390 --> 00:08:47,390
preparing a birthday party for him,

144
00:08:47,970 --> 00:08:48,880
my husband

145
00:08:49,250 --> 00:08:51,000
left the country

146
00:08:50,570 --> 00:08:57,080
♫When the wind blows into the sea♫

147
00:08:51,000 --> 00:08:52,530
with my best friend, Wen Li.

148
00:08:53,610 --> 00:08:55,330
Opportunity and disaster

149
00:08:55,670 --> 00:08:57,770
struck me at the same time.

150
00:08:58,080 --> 00:09:00,980
♫The clouds are scattered♫

151
00:09:02,580 --> 00:09:10,040
♫No one can tell my feelings♫

152
00:09:08,530 --> 00:09:09,240
Liu Ming.

153
00:09:09,770 --> 00:09:10,900
Let's get a divorce.

154
00:09:10,930 --> 00:09:13,890
♫There's a future♫

155
00:09:15,440 --> 00:09:17,310
I passed the bar exam.

156
00:09:15,490 --> 00:09:19,350
♫From one to two♫

157
00:09:17,630 --> 00:09:19,100
I'll be in law from now on.

158
00:09:20,070 --> 00:09:22,270
♫In destitution, it's time♫

159
00:09:20,490 --> 00:09:22,010
You...

160
00:09:22,010 --> 00:09:23,360
Tell me. I got you?

161
00:09:22,960 --> 00:09:26,580
♫to put away my insignificant emotions♫

162
00:09:23,360 --> 00:09:24,000
Right?

163
00:09:24,130 --> 00:09:25,100
Yes. You got me.

164
00:09:25,130 --> 00:09:25,900
I'm telling you.

165
00:09:25,900 --> 00:09:27,060
If we were truly going to divorce,

166
00:09:27,060 --> 00:09:29,230
I'd sue you and clean out your account.

167
00:09:29,880 --> 00:09:31,830
Do you know how difficult the bar exam is?

168
00:09:31,830 --> 00:09:33,360
The passing rate is only 7%.

169
00:09:33,490 --> 00:09:34,650
But I passed.

170
00:09:34,850 --> 00:09:35,980
Am I awesome or what?

171
00:09:36,330 --> 00:09:36,890
Yingzi.

172
00:09:37,130 --> 00:09:38,190
You're so amazing.

173
00:09:38,300 --> 00:09:40,590
Of course. You married an amazing woman.

174
00:09:41,550 --> 00:09:42,080
Go to work.

175
00:09:42,080 --> 00:09:42,680
By the way,

176
00:09:43,030 --> 00:09:44,090
come back home early today.

177
00:09:44,090 --> 00:09:45,200
It's your 30th birthday.

178
00:09:45,200 --> 00:09:46,610
We should celebrate it.

179
00:09:48,120 --> 00:09:48,890
Go.

180
00:09:59,140 --> 00:10:01,130
♫Fly♫

181
00:10:02,370 --> 00:10:05,120
♫In the middle of nowhere♫

182
00:10:06,560 --> 00:10:08,940
♫I thought we could be together forever♫

183
00:10:09,280 --> 00:10:13,770
♫Turns out it's just a friendly kiss♫

184
00:10:16,040 --> 00:10:17,060
Goodbye, Yingzi.

185
00:10:17,330 --> 00:10:19,840
♫Only the kite is missed♫

186
00:10:19,870 --> 00:10:22,230
♫Trapped at the starting point♫

187
00:10:23,730 --> 00:10:26,470
♫If I were a bird♫

188
00:10:27,970 --> 00:10:32,460
♫I wouldn't be afraid of distance♫

189
00:10:33,120 --> 00:10:35,370
♫The wind blows♫

190
00:10:36,680 --> 00:10:39,800
♫And I'll leave♫

191
00:10:40,940 --> 00:10:44,050
♫Fly to the deep sea♫

192
00:10:45,230 --> 00:10:52,630
♫In the long night, find a pure white wave♫

193
00:10:53,780 --> 00:10:57,150
♫That future♫

194
00:10:58,080 --> 00:11:01,620
♫Farewell♫

195
00:11:02,370 --> 00:11:09,950
♫There'll be something amazing waiting for me♫

196
00:11:11,000 --> 00:11:19,610
♫I see someone waiting in the light♫

197
00:11:17,420 --> 00:11:18,780
Look at your answers.

198
00:11:19,710 --> 00:11:21,090
So ridiculous!

199
00:11:22,300 --> 00:11:23,780
You think

200
00:11:24,330 --> 00:11:25,790
you could become lawyers?

201
00:11:27,210 --> 00:11:29,130
What do you think the law is for?

202
00:11:30,040 --> 00:11:31,040
To make ends meet?

203
00:11:31,120 --> 00:11:32,360
To make a living?

204
00:11:34,130 --> 00:11:35,760
My patience is limited.

205
00:11:36,730 --> 00:11:38,480
If you keep doing this,

206
00:11:39,410 --> 00:11:40,960
you'd better drop out.

207
00:11:41,190 --> 00:11:42,300
Don't come to my class.

208
00:11:42,300 --> 00:11:43,300
The class is over.

209
00:11:48,790 --> 00:11:49,580
I want to drop out too,

210
00:11:49,580 --> 00:11:50,730
but you have to refund the tuition fee to us.

211
00:11:50,730 --> 00:11:51,480
Exactly.

212
00:11:51,480 --> 00:11:54,280
Always act like she has devoted herself to the law.

213
00:11:54,330 --> 00:11:56,190
Then why are you here teaching us?

214
00:12:13,210 --> 00:12:14,270
Congratulations.

215
00:12:16,200 --> 00:12:17,470
Congratulations?

216
00:12:18,250 --> 00:12:21,490
Didn't you pass the bar exam?

217
00:12:24,330 --> 00:12:24,910
Yes.

218
00:12:25,560 --> 00:12:27,380
Thank you, Mrs. Mei.

219
00:12:29,610 --> 00:12:30,610
Something wrong?

220
00:12:33,110 --> 00:12:33,750
Mrs. Mei.

221
00:12:43,600 --> 00:12:44,330
Come in.

222
00:12:49,850 --> 00:12:50,610
Mrs. Mei.

223
00:12:54,960 --> 00:12:57,160
My husband ran away with another woman.

224
00:12:59,210 --> 00:13:00,130
I always thought

225
00:13:00,130 --> 00:13:02,210
we were happily married.

226
00:13:03,700 --> 00:13:04,980
But now I found out

227
00:13:05,010 --> 00:13:08,360
that I was living a big lie.

228
00:13:06,380 --> 00:13:10,130
[Judicial Exam Teacher, Mei Daliang]

229
00:13:09,600 --> 00:13:12,050
I'm surrounded by lies and deception.

230
00:13:12,080 --> 00:13:14,970
My husband, my parents-in-law, and my best friend.

231
00:13:15,010 --> 00:13:17,330
They worked together to lie to me.

232
00:13:18,110 --> 00:13:19,230
I don't know

233
00:13:19,250 --> 00:13:20,360
what I did wrong.

234
00:13:22,150 --> 00:13:23,910
I think I'm a good woman.

235
00:13:24,410 --> 00:13:25,400
These days...

236
00:13:26,610 --> 00:13:28,850
I don't know who I can talk to.

237
00:13:29,190 --> 00:13:31,790
I can't tell these things to my parents either.

238
00:13:32,490 --> 00:13:33,400
It seems...

239
00:13:34,640 --> 00:13:36,570
that they shouldn't have given you

240
00:13:36,890 --> 00:13:38,250
that entrance ticket.

241
00:13:40,000 --> 00:13:41,390
A law student

242
00:13:42,010 --> 00:13:43,610
who passed the bar exam

243
00:13:43,710 --> 00:13:44,890
but only knows

244
00:13:45,120 --> 00:13:46,400
to cry to someone...

245
00:13:47,530 --> 00:13:49,010
when something happens.

246
00:13:52,250 --> 00:13:53,360
People like you

247
00:13:54,000 --> 00:13:55,640
won't become good lawyers

248
00:13:56,410 --> 00:13:58,250
even if they pass the bar exam.

249
00:14:00,370 --> 00:14:02,490
But you have to let me cry and vent

250
00:14:03,130 --> 00:14:05,490
when such a big thing happens!

251
00:14:06,360 --> 00:14:07,980
Who wants to listen to your story?

252
00:14:07,980 --> 00:14:09,490
Who is obligated to listen to your story?

253
00:14:09,490 --> 00:14:11,690
Can you win back your husband by crying?

254
00:14:14,120 --> 00:14:16,050
While you're sitting here crying,

255
00:14:16,240 --> 00:14:18,320
your husband and your best friend

256
00:14:18,490 --> 00:14:20,000
may be transferring the assets

257
00:14:20,000 --> 00:14:22,090
that you still have.

258
00:14:22,740 --> 00:14:25,580
Everything you have will be taken away.

259
00:14:25,610 --> 00:14:26,320
Thank you.

260
00:14:30,720 --> 00:14:32,980
You'd better tear that certificate off.

261
00:14:33,130 --> 00:14:33,720
Go.

262
00:14:34,610 --> 00:14:35,730
I don't have a student like you.

263
00:14:35,730 --> 00:14:37,300
You don't have to come to me anymore.

264
00:14:37,300 --> 00:14:37,980
Leave.

265
00:14:38,010 --> 00:14:39,600
Well, Mrs. Mei,

266
00:14:40,130 --> 00:14:40,840
I'm sorry.

267
00:14:41,720 --> 00:14:43,400
My brain was blanked just now.

268
00:14:44,240 --> 00:14:45,770
I'll go figure out a way now.

269
00:14:48,060 --> 00:14:48,740
Wait!

270
00:14:55,210 --> 00:14:56,400
In life,

271
00:14:59,120 --> 00:15:01,130
many things will happen.

272
00:15:04,360 --> 00:15:06,090
As long as you remain standing,

273
00:15:07,200 --> 00:15:08,720
no one can defeat you.

274
00:15:11,410 --> 00:15:13,540
As long as you still stand on your feet,

275
00:15:15,120 --> 00:15:16,760
you can defeat your opponent

276
00:15:18,640 --> 00:15:20,170
and the person who hurt you.

277
00:15:42,930 --> 00:15:45,290
This is the phone number of my old law firm.

278
00:15:46,330 --> 00:15:47,610
They're hiring.

279
00:15:48,370 --> 00:15:50,360
You've passed the bar exam.

280
00:15:52,230 --> 00:15:52,830
Go.

281
00:15:53,720 --> 00:15:55,130
Stand up again.

282
00:15:56,440 --> 00:15:58,650
Protect yourself with the law.

283
00:16:30,250 --> 00:16:31,250
Just like before.

284
00:16:31,960 --> 00:16:33,280
Let's get down to business.

285
